Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C and remove your @21 Day Aged British Sirloin Steaks{2} from
the fridge to allow it to come up to room temperature. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm
chunks (no need to peel).

Pop the potatoes on a large low-sided wide #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, then
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.
Once your oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}. Turn
halfway through cooking.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary, you want the potatoes nicely spread out.

Meanwhile, halve, peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}. Crush the
@black peppercorns{} in a #pestle and mortar{}. 

> TIP: You can also put them in a freezer bag and give them a whack with a rolling pin.

Trim the @green beans{150%g} and pop onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. When the potatoes have 10 mins left, put the green
beans on the middle shelf of your oven and roast until tender, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Season the steaks with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. When the oil is hot, lay the steaks in the pan and brown for
~{1%minute} on each side.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Lower the heat slightly and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes} on each side for medium-rare.
> TIP: Cook for 1-2 mins more if you like it more cooked.

> IMPORTANT: The steak is safe to eat when the outside is browned.

Once cooked, transfer to a #board{}, cover with @foil{} and leave to rest for a
couple of minutes.

Add a little @oil{} to the now-empty frying pan and turn the heat to low. Add the
shallot. Cook until soft, ~{2-3%minutes}. Add the peppercorns. Cook for ~{1%minute},
then stir in the @water for the sauce{75%ml} and @chicken stock paste{10%g}. Bring to
the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-3%minutes}. Take
the pan off the heat and stir in the @crème fraîche{75%g}.

Slice the steak diagonally into 1cm strips and transfer to your #plates{}. Drizzle
over the peppercorn sauce and serve with the green beans and roasted potatoes
alongside. Enjoy!